1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:03,718 --> 00:00:04,686
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

3
00:00:04,686 --> 00:00:06,087
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

4
00:00:06,087 --> 00:00:07,155
(Scenes with child actors
followed production guidelines.)

5
00:00:13,094 --> 00:00:14,829
You sent the seedlings at least, right?

6
00:00:16,131 --> 00:00:18,166
Yes, thanks to you telling me
about the air holes,

7
00:00:18,166 --> 00:00:19,534
I safely delivered them.

8
00:00:21,069 --> 00:00:22,037
Great work.

9
00:00:22,704 --> 00:00:25,273
Now you can finally stand
a little taller, right?

10
00:00:25,273 --> 00:00:27,475
It must feel rewarding to become like...

11
00:00:27,475 --> 00:00:28,943
those animals at Mat Story, doesn't it?

12
00:00:28,943 --> 00:00:31,112
That's a bit harsh, don't you think?

13
00:00:31,513 --> 00:00:34,315
I'm just doing my best in my position.

14
00:00:34,683 --> 00:00:35,550
Your best?

15
00:00:37,118 --> 00:00:39,320
Is exploiting the villagers your best?

16
00:00:40,288 --> 00:00:44,292
True. If you want your sons
to recognize you as their father,

17
00:00:44,292 --> 00:00:45,894
I guess licking Mat Story's boots
is the way to go.

18
00:00:45,894 --> 00:00:47,429
What's a little shame, right?

19
00:00:47,429 --> 00:00:48,697
What about Mat Story?

20
00:00:49,264 --> 00:00:53,068
Mat Story is a company
that strictly follows its manuals.

21
00:00:54,235 --> 00:00:57,305
You're an even bigger idiot
than I thought.

22
00:00:57,605 --> 00:01:00,475
They demoted you,
and yet, you're still defending them?

23
00:01:00,475 --> 00:01:02,744
I'm embarrassed for you.

24
00:01:03,311 --> 00:01:04,679
Why you little...

25
00:01:33,208 --> 00:01:34,442
(Sunny Hair)

26
00:01:34,442 --> 00:01:36,277
My goodness.

27
00:01:36,277 --> 00:01:39,848
You're glowing.

28
00:01:39,848 --> 00:01:42,684
You're such a handsome officer.

29
00:01:42,684 --> 00:01:44,552
Who's going to snatch you up?

30
00:01:46,421 --> 00:01:48,323
What do you think about me, Mother-in-law?

31
00:01:49,257 --> 00:01:50,625
What are you saying?

32
00:01:51,259 --> 00:01:52,494
You're a police officer.

33
00:01:52,494 --> 00:01:54,562
You shouldn't surprise me like that
without signaling first.

34
00:01:57,065 --> 00:01:59,300
Hye Sun. Hye Sun.

35
00:01:59,300 --> 00:02:00,468
Come on.

36
00:02:00,468 --> 00:02:02,137
Why are you making such a fuss again?

37
00:02:02,137 --> 00:02:03,605
Hear me out.

38
00:02:03,605 --> 00:02:05,106
Do you know what I just saw?

39
00:02:08,243 --> 00:02:10,478
Has Bo Mi lost her mind?

40
00:02:10,478 --> 00:02:12,714
Love is overflowing everywhere.

41
00:02:13,314 --> 00:02:15,717
Don't be ridiculous. This is war now.

42
00:02:17,152 --> 00:02:19,754
The eldest son of Mat Story and Bo Mi...

43
00:02:19,754 --> 00:02:21,723
were on a date.

44
00:02:23,324 --> 00:02:24,626
The eldest son of Mat Story?

45
00:02:26,294 --> 00:02:27,195
You mean Seong Ji Cheon?

46
00:02:28,329 --> 00:02:31,633
Actually... Now that I think about it,
it wasn't a date.

47
00:02:31,633 --> 00:02:32,534
It wasn't a date.

48
00:02:36,037 --> 00:02:38,506
I have to work, so I'll get going now.

49
00:02:38,506 --> 00:02:40,341
Okay. Bye.

50
00:02:41,009 --> 00:02:42,377
By the way...

51
00:02:42,911 --> 00:02:43,912
You see...

52
00:02:44,312 --> 00:02:45,747
But...

53
00:02:45,747 --> 00:02:46,848
Okay, sure.

54
00:02:46,848 --> 00:02:49,718
But you need to pay...

55
00:02:49,718 --> 00:02:52,287
Hye Sun, what do we do?

56
00:02:52,287 --> 00:02:53,755
Did you see Officer Park's face?

57
00:02:55,190 --> 00:02:57,625
Where did you see those two?

58
00:02:57,625 --> 00:02:58,660
Well...

59
00:02:59,527 --> 00:03:02,630
That's not the issue.
Aren't you worried at all?

60
00:03:02,630 --> 00:03:03,631
Come on.

61
00:03:04,199 --> 00:03:07,702
My husband's eyes burn with rage
just hearing the word Mat Story.

62
00:03:09,003 --> 00:03:12,407
If Bo Mi had her head on straight,
she wouldn't be doing something like that.

63
00:03:13,441 --> 00:03:16,277
But what if it's true?

64
00:03:23,685 --> 00:03:25,186
- Ji Cheon.
- Yes?

65
00:03:26,521 --> 00:03:27,355
Well...

66
00:03:28,390 --> 00:03:30,191
What you said before...

67
00:03:30,191 --> 00:03:31,860
About not going back to Seoul.

68
00:03:33,895 --> 00:03:35,764
Did you really mean...

69
00:03:40,468 --> 00:03:43,772
What if the two of them...

70
00:03:44,572 --> 00:03:46,541
are truly involved?

71
00:03:49,377 --> 00:03:50,311
Then...

72
00:03:51,546 --> 00:03:52,981
that'll be the day...

73
00:03:54,082 --> 00:03:56,751
a whole family disappears
from this village.

74
00:03:57,719 --> 00:04:00,321
See? Your true colors are showing now.

75
00:04:00,822 --> 00:04:03,591
In the end, you're just
another Mat Story animal.

76
00:04:05,527 --> 00:04:08,430
You repay enemies with kindness
and kindness with betrayal.

77
00:04:08,430 --> 00:04:09,998
It's not even worth punching you.

78
00:04:10,765 --> 00:04:12,133
Kindness?

79
00:04:12,133 --> 00:04:15,003
What kindness have you shown me?

80
00:04:15,003 --> 00:04:17,706
The hardware store, the co-op...

81
00:04:17,706 --> 00:04:20,742
Even during the flooding...
Did you do anything but interfere?

82
00:04:20,742 --> 00:04:22,444
No. I haven't even started
interfering yet.

83
00:04:22,444 --> 00:04:23,678
You want me to show you
what that looks like?

84
00:04:24,713 --> 00:04:26,481
Are you threatening me right now?

85
00:04:26,481 --> 00:04:28,783
You think this is a threat?

86
00:04:28,783 --> 00:04:29,918
It's a warning.

87
00:04:29,918 --> 00:04:32,354
Then keep going. Say more.

88
00:04:32,354 --> 00:04:36,124
I will tear your whole field apart.

89
00:04:36,791 --> 00:04:38,159
Tear it apart?

90
00:04:38,159 --> 00:04:39,094
That's what I'll do.

91
00:04:40,328 --> 00:04:41,229
You think being tall is all that?

92
00:04:42,497 --> 00:04:44,099
I can lift you in one move and...

93
00:04:45,100 --> 00:04:47,936
What? You can't lift me.
With just one finger...

94
00:04:57,345 --> 00:04:59,748
Ji Cheon, just now...

95
00:05:01,683 --> 00:05:02,584
I'm sorry.

96
00:05:02,851 --> 00:05:03,785
What?

97
00:05:03,785 --> 00:05:05,253
What I mean is...

98
00:05:06,154 --> 00:05:08,923
I didn't mean to do it.

99
00:05:09,224 --> 00:05:12,027
Yes, I did mean to do it, but...

100
00:05:16,064 --> 00:05:17,198
What?

101
00:05:17,632 --> 00:05:18,933
What is this?

102
00:05:21,102 --> 00:05:22,070
Come on.

103
00:05:22,904 --> 00:05:24,172
I'll just...

104
00:05:24,172 --> 00:05:25,440
Did you touch me?

105
00:05:28,276 --> 00:05:30,612
- Right hook.
- Go ahead and hit me.

106
00:05:30,612 --> 00:05:31,479
Dad?

107
00:05:34,349 --> 00:05:35,150
Dad.

108
00:05:35,150 --> 00:05:37,952
- For the past five years.
- You boxed for five years?

109
00:05:37,952 --> 00:05:39,621
Let go of me.

110
00:05:39,621 --> 00:05:42,691
- Why you little...
- I've trained for years in boxing.

111
00:05:42,691 --> 00:05:43,925
You...

112
00:05:43,925 --> 00:05:46,494
I'll smash your head in.

113
00:05:46,494 --> 00:05:48,596
I'll throw a spinning kick.

114
00:05:48,596 --> 00:05:50,031
You're too slow.

115
00:05:50,031 --> 00:05:51,766
I'll smash your head.

116
00:05:52,901 --> 00:05:57,505
(EP 5 The Truth is Unclear,
Feelings are Overflowing)

117
00:05:59,140 --> 00:06:02,210
Let go of me. Unbelievable.

118
00:06:02,210 --> 00:06:03,044
What?

119
00:06:04,012 --> 00:06:05,280
Were you in a fight?

120
00:06:05,280 --> 00:06:07,282
Right in front of our house.
With the village chief.

121
00:06:07,282 --> 00:06:08,683
I wouldn't call it a fight.

122
00:06:08,683 --> 00:06:11,086
It was more like I handled him.

123
00:06:11,386 --> 00:06:14,389
That village chief is a terrible man.

124
00:06:15,690 --> 00:06:17,125
You fought with the village chief?

125
00:06:17,125 --> 00:06:19,894
He messed with my pride.

126
00:06:19,894 --> 00:06:21,796
He insulted Mat Story.

127
00:06:21,796 --> 00:06:24,699
I'm a man who's lived with pride
in my work for the past 20 years.

128
00:06:24,699 --> 00:06:25,667
You know that.

129
00:06:25,667 --> 00:06:28,303
Even so, how can two grown men fight?

130
00:06:29,404 --> 00:06:32,774
And you already know
that if you get on his bad side here,

131
00:06:32,774 --> 00:06:34,509
you're the one who'll suffer.

132
00:06:34,843 --> 00:06:36,945
Successfully farm the cabbage quickly...

133
00:06:36,945 --> 00:06:38,813
and go back to Seoul as soon as possible.

134
00:06:38,813 --> 00:06:41,449
If he's got something to say,
he should bring proof.

135
00:06:41,449 --> 00:06:43,418
He keeps picking fights,
bringing up the past over and over.

136
00:06:43,418 --> 00:06:44,886
I can't take it anymore.

137
00:06:44,886 --> 00:06:47,489
It's war with them now.

138
00:06:47,922 --> 00:06:50,392
Seong Ji Cheon.
You get yourself together too, okay?

139
00:06:51,092 --> 00:06:51,926
Me?

140
00:06:52,160 --> 00:06:53,661
Why me? Just like that?

141
00:06:53,661 --> 00:06:55,063
Just get yourself together.

142
00:06:55,630 --> 00:06:57,365
Don't go near their place.

143
00:07:00,368 --> 00:07:01,236
Ji Cheon.

144
00:07:02,037 --> 00:07:03,071
What?

145
00:07:03,071 --> 00:07:03,905
Goodness.

146
00:07:05,807 --> 00:07:06,908
My neck's all stiff now.

147
00:07:10,045 --> 00:07:11,680
Your glasses broke.

148
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:13,114
What a mess. This is ridiculous.

149
00:07:13,915 --> 00:07:15,083
Yes, my glasses broke.

150
00:07:15,083 --> 00:07:17,218
But if I had really punched him,
he wouldn't be able to get up.

151
00:07:17,218 --> 00:07:18,119
That's cold.

152
00:07:19,821 --> 00:07:22,490
You went up against someone from Seoul...

153
00:07:23,091 --> 00:07:25,093
and sprained your shoulder?

154
00:07:26,161 --> 00:07:29,597
Im Ju Hyeong, you've lost it now.

155
00:07:29,597 --> 00:07:30,965
You poor thing.

156
00:07:30,965 --> 00:07:33,268
This is so embarrassing for you.

157
00:07:35,503 --> 00:07:38,506
I'm totally fine.

158
00:07:39,207 --> 00:07:41,342
Why did I even help plow his field?

159
00:07:44,846 --> 00:07:46,748
- You did what?
- What?

160
00:07:46,748 --> 00:07:50,418
What did I say?

161
00:07:50,418 --> 00:07:52,787
Do we still have my old glasses somewhere?

162
00:07:53,355 --> 00:07:55,757
Seriously...

163
00:07:56,224 --> 00:07:59,561
You two aren't little kids. Unbelievable.

164
00:07:59,828 --> 00:08:02,597
Just be glad that the police
won't be calling you tomorrow.

165
00:08:03,231 --> 00:08:06,101
The police. Fine by me.
I'm a victim, too.

166
00:08:06,101 --> 00:08:07,869
Either way, Seong Tae Hun is finished.

167
00:08:07,869 --> 00:08:08,937
He's out.

168
00:08:08,937 --> 00:08:10,772
It's over now. He's out.

169
00:08:15,543 --> 00:08:17,078
Did you get home safely?

170
00:08:17,078 --> 00:08:18,780
Is your father okay?

171
00:08:21,683 --> 00:08:22,884
Don't even ask.

172
00:08:22,884 --> 00:08:25,453
He was making a fuss for a while,
but I think he finally fell asleep.

173
00:08:26,855 --> 00:08:28,623
What about your father?

174
00:08:28,623 --> 00:08:29,858
Was he hurt badly?

175
00:08:31,559 --> 00:08:33,962
He was exaggerating. He'll be fine.

176
00:08:35,530 --> 00:08:37,232
Get some sleep for now.

177
00:08:38,033 --> 00:08:39,000
What happened today...

178
00:08:47,375 --> 00:08:48,743
Let's talk about it face-to-face tomorrow.

179
00:08:50,145 --> 00:08:52,547
Okay. You sleep well too, Bo Mi.

180
00:08:52,547 --> 00:08:53,682
See you at school tomorrow.

181
00:09:05,493 --> 00:09:09,397
The dopamine levels have exceeded
the threshold.

182
00:09:10,465 --> 00:09:13,568
This is clearly an overload...

183
00:09:15,270 --> 00:09:17,172
Seong Ji Cheon. Forever single...

184
00:09:19,708 --> 00:09:20,575
Ji Sang Gu.

185
00:09:22,277 --> 00:09:23,111
You're not asleep?

186
00:09:26,114 --> 00:09:26,981
I guess you are.

187
00:09:38,493 --> 00:09:40,295
How are his lips that soft?

188
00:09:42,697 --> 00:09:44,299
And his skin is so fair.

189
00:09:45,700 --> 00:09:48,636
Do people from Seoul naturally have
soft lips like that?

190
00:09:51,673 --> 00:09:53,074
I must be losing my mind.

191
00:09:59,280 --> 00:10:00,682
Watching you raising kids in nature...

192
00:10:00,682 --> 00:10:02,384
Just watching you is truly healing.

193
00:10:02,384 --> 00:10:03,585
Your lifestyle is my dream.

194
00:10:03,585 --> 00:10:05,120
Even just from the photos,
the air feels different.

195
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:06,688
Not everyone gets to experience
this kind of healing in nature.

196
00:10:06,688 --> 00:10:10,258
I heard in a Toronto Korean moms'
community...

197
00:10:10,258 --> 00:10:11,926
that because of
her kids' education costs...

198
00:10:11,926 --> 00:10:12,727
Delete.

199
00:10:17,032 --> 00:10:18,066
Where are you?

200
00:10:19,367 --> 00:10:20,935
Pay me back, you wench.

201
00:10:27,409 --> 00:10:28,676
You scared me.

202
00:10:29,411 --> 00:10:31,846
Honey, it's me.

203
00:10:32,614 --> 00:10:35,350
What are you doing in the dark bathroom?

204
00:10:36,084 --> 00:10:37,752
I...

205
00:10:37,752 --> 00:10:40,422
I guess I drank too much water last night.

206
00:10:40,689 --> 00:10:42,524
Why are you up so early?

207
00:10:43,725 --> 00:10:44,826
Are you hurt?

208
00:10:45,226 --> 00:10:47,996
I'm fine.

209
00:10:47,996 --> 00:10:49,631
But I need to get to the field early.

210
00:10:49,631 --> 00:10:51,499
Who knows what the village chief
might've done?

211
00:10:51,499 --> 00:10:54,169
I see. Hurry up and wash up.

212
00:10:54,169 --> 00:10:55,103
- Okay.
- Okay.

213
00:11:10,051 --> 00:11:10,952
Hey.

214
00:11:13,822 --> 00:11:16,958
I'm sorry about what happened last night
between you and my husband.

215
00:11:17,592 --> 00:11:19,494
Are you feeling okay?

216
00:11:20,295 --> 00:11:23,765
I'm a little sore.

217
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:28,770
Then why are you heading out
to the field this early?

218
00:11:29,971 --> 00:11:30,772
Then again,

219
00:11:31,239 --> 00:11:34,008
my husband left at dawn too.

220
00:11:34,476 --> 00:11:38,079
You're both still young, aren't you?

221
00:11:38,947 --> 00:11:40,582
He left already?

222
00:11:41,116 --> 00:11:41,850
Yes.

223
00:11:44,285 --> 00:11:45,153
Wait.

224
00:11:46,788 --> 00:11:47,622
What was that?

225
00:11:57,465 --> 00:11:58,900
What's this?

226
00:13:05,767 --> 00:13:06,634
They've sprouted.

227
00:13:06,968 --> 00:13:08,503
I see cabbage sprouts.

228
00:13:09,504 --> 00:13:10,338
I...

229
00:13:12,140 --> 00:13:14,509
No, my entire family worked hard
to grow them.

230
00:13:16,644 --> 00:13:17,879
How could this happen...

231
00:13:18,580 --> 00:13:20,648
Who...

232
00:13:21,383 --> 00:13:24,285
I will tear your whole field apart.

233
00:13:44,606 --> 00:13:45,840
Why is he sitting there like that?

234
00:13:49,010 --> 00:13:50,011
Dad, are you okay?

235
00:13:50,879 --> 00:13:51,980
Let me take a look, Dad.

236
00:13:53,281 --> 00:13:55,083
Shouldn't you go see a doctor?

237
00:13:55,083 --> 00:13:56,718
I'm fine.

238
00:13:56,718 --> 00:13:58,219
Come on. Let me take a look.

239
00:13:58,219 --> 00:13:59,454
Did you pull something?

240
00:13:59,454 --> 00:14:01,890
I said I'm fine.

241
00:14:01,890 --> 00:14:05,727
Last night, you were all talk,
acting tough.

242
00:14:06,161 --> 00:14:06,995
What happened?

243
00:14:07,962 --> 00:14:09,364
If it's this bad for me,

244
00:14:09,731 --> 00:14:12,634
I'm sure Tae Hun can't even
get up right now.

245
00:14:13,268 --> 00:14:14,869
Dream on.

246
00:14:15,170 --> 00:14:16,671
I saw him earlier.

247
00:14:16,671 --> 00:14:19,207
He was already heading to the field
just fine.

248
00:14:19,207 --> 00:14:20,975
- What?
- Which reminds me...

249
00:14:21,876 --> 00:14:25,580
Where were you at the crack of dawn?

250
00:14:26,648 --> 00:14:27,482
Chief!

251
00:14:28,149 --> 00:14:29,217
You jerk.

252
00:14:31,119 --> 00:14:32,153
What was that?

253
00:14:32,153 --> 00:14:34,055
This voice...

254
00:14:35,857 --> 00:14:36,958
You jerk.

255
00:14:39,027 --> 00:14:39,928
My cabbages...

256
00:14:40,762 --> 00:14:44,132
You really trampled
all my precious cabbages?

257
00:14:44,132 --> 00:14:45,667
I won't put up with this anymore.

258
00:14:46,101 --> 00:14:47,769
Your cabbages? What about them?

259
00:14:47,769 --> 00:14:50,672
You turned my field into a complete mess!

260
00:14:51,506 --> 00:14:53,541
You're the one who's a real mess.

261
00:14:53,541 --> 00:14:54,776
Explain slowly. What happened?

262
00:14:54,776 --> 00:14:56,177
Hey, listen.

263
00:14:56,177 --> 00:14:58,113
Why don't you calm down first?

264
00:14:58,113 --> 00:14:59,481
Don't play dumb.

265
00:14:59,948 --> 00:15:01,850
You said it yourself last night...

266
00:15:01,850 --> 00:15:04,085
that you'd tear my field apart.

267
00:15:04,085 --> 00:15:07,222
This is a violation of private property
and obstruction of business.

268
00:15:07,222 --> 00:15:09,424
Private property? Obstruction of business?

269
00:15:10,492 --> 00:15:11,726
Hey, Seong Tae Hun.

270
00:15:11,726 --> 00:15:14,396
I don't know
what happened to your field, but...

271
00:15:14,396 --> 00:15:15,463
Do you have proof?

272
00:15:15,463 --> 00:15:16,731
Did you find my fingerprints or something?

273
00:15:17,198 --> 00:15:17,999
Honey.

274
00:15:17,999 --> 00:15:20,735
I wasn't going to say this,
but you listen carefully, Seong Tae Hun.

275
00:15:20,735 --> 00:15:21,736
- What?
- Dad.

276
00:15:21,736 --> 00:15:22,937
No matter what I do,

277
00:15:22,937 --> 00:15:25,240
I'd never do something
as filthy as Mat Story.

278
00:15:25,240 --> 00:15:26,741
Even when they fined our whole village...

279
00:15:26,741 --> 00:15:28,676
just because a tiny amount of pesticide
was detected,

280
00:15:28,676 --> 00:15:31,513
even when they put many of our villagers
in debt and kicked them out,

281
00:15:31,513 --> 00:15:32,647
and even when I realized...

282
00:15:32,647 --> 00:15:35,350
it was all a setup to drive down
contract prices...

283
00:15:35,350 --> 00:15:37,218
I didn't stoop to your level.

284
00:15:37,218 --> 00:15:39,020
I just wanted to grow
the cabbage successfully...

285
00:15:39,020 --> 00:15:41,523
to prove our village was innocent.

286
00:15:41,523 --> 00:15:42,590
So what did you just accuse me of?

287
00:15:42,590 --> 00:15:44,292
Destroying your field?

288
00:15:44,292 --> 00:15:45,460
How dare you!

289
00:15:45,460 --> 00:15:46,795
If you felt wronged,

290
00:15:46,795 --> 00:15:49,864
you should've taken it to
the co-op or handled it legally.

291
00:15:49,864 --> 00:15:51,733
Why are you taking your anger out
about the past...

292
00:15:51,733 --> 00:15:54,102
on someone who had nothing to do with it?

293
00:16:01,910 --> 00:16:04,913
There's no one as kind as my husband.

294
00:16:04,913 --> 00:16:07,749
Chief. I think you've been
going too far lately...

295
00:16:07,749 --> 00:16:09,351
- over past issues.
- That's right.

296
00:16:09,351 --> 00:16:10,885
You even punched him last night.

297
00:16:10,885 --> 00:16:13,355
What did you say? Punched?

298
00:16:13,688 --> 00:16:17,192
My boy's back is bruised right now...

299
00:16:17,192 --> 00:16:19,594
so it's covered in pain patches.

300
00:16:19,594 --> 00:16:23,465
Even then, I was worried about
your husband.

301
00:16:23,465 --> 00:16:25,166
You're really pushing it now...

302
00:16:25,166 --> 00:16:27,001
Who are you calling a boy?

303
00:16:30,572 --> 00:16:32,707
- Why are you yelling like that?
- Mom.

304
00:16:32,707 --> 00:16:34,275
Let's not do this anymore.

305
00:16:34,275 --> 00:16:35,777
You too, Dad. That's enough.

306
00:16:36,010 --> 00:16:39,247
I'll find evidence and go to the police.

307
00:16:39,247 --> 00:16:40,115
So you better be ready.

308
00:16:40,115 --> 00:16:41,149
Let's go.

309
00:16:41,149 --> 00:16:42,817
I'll sue you for defamation.

310
00:16:42,817 --> 00:16:43,918
- Defamation?
- Where are you going?

311
00:16:43,918 --> 00:16:45,520
What honor do you even have?

312
00:16:50,358 --> 00:16:51,426
I've boxed...

313
00:16:51,426 --> 00:16:53,228
Don't you dare run off!

314
00:16:53,228 --> 00:16:54,195
Boxing...

315
00:16:55,196 --> 00:16:56,331
That's enough, Dad.

316
00:16:56,331 --> 00:16:58,466
Let go. Let go.

317
00:16:59,801 --> 00:17:01,369
I'm the incumbent chief.

318
00:17:01,369 --> 00:17:02,537
Let go.

319
00:17:02,537 --> 00:17:04,672
Come here right now!

320
00:17:04,672 --> 00:17:06,408
Why you little...

321
00:17:06,408 --> 00:17:08,676
That's enough.

322
00:17:20,989 --> 00:17:22,357
Data doesn't lie.

323
00:17:23,124 --> 00:17:26,194
A culprit always leaves traces.

324
00:17:27,128 --> 00:17:28,596
So I'll be sure to find out the truth.

325
00:17:28,596 --> 00:17:30,665
My family worked so hard in this field.

326
00:17:31,499 --> 00:17:33,902
A culprit always leaves traces.

327
00:17:39,808 --> 00:17:40,875
I found it.

328
00:17:40,875 --> 00:17:42,177
This must be the culprit's footprint.

329
00:17:42,844 --> 00:17:44,012
It's smaller than mine.

330
00:17:44,679 --> 00:17:46,715
Roughly size 250-260?

331
00:17:47,549 --> 00:17:48,416
Maybe 260?

332
00:17:55,323 --> 00:17:57,692
You see this, right? A human footprint.

333
00:17:58,226 --> 00:18:00,261
I'm certain it was the village chief.

334
00:18:00,729 --> 00:18:03,865
It does look like a human footprint,

335
00:18:03,865 --> 00:18:05,967
but to say
that it's the village chief's...

336
00:18:08,203 --> 00:18:10,438
I thought you'd be different, officer.

337
00:18:10,839 --> 00:18:14,409
Are even the police
on the village chief's side here?

338
00:18:14,409 --> 00:18:15,844
He clearly said it himself...

339
00:18:15,844 --> 00:18:18,813
that he'll tear my field apart.

340
00:18:18,813 --> 00:18:20,382
Sir, please calm down.

341
00:18:21,116 --> 00:18:24,619
At least show me
the security camera footage.

342
00:18:24,619 --> 00:18:27,655
Due to circumstances, I can't report this
to my company right now,

343
00:18:27,655 --> 00:18:29,357
so not our field's security cameras.

344
00:18:29,357 --> 00:18:31,860
But at least show me footage
of nearby security cameras.

345
00:18:32,160 --> 00:18:35,263
If you're truly a fair officer...

346
00:18:35,764 --> 00:18:39,000
The only security cameras in that area
belong to the village chief.

347
00:18:39,801 --> 00:18:40,835
One moment, please.

348
00:18:51,312 --> 00:18:52,213
Yes?

349
00:18:52,213 --> 00:18:53,948
Chief. This is Officer Park.

350
00:18:53,948 --> 00:18:54,816
Yes?

351
00:18:56,151 --> 00:18:58,920
Mr. Seong Tae Hun from Mat Story is here.

352
00:18:59,220 --> 00:19:01,990
We need to check the footage
of the security cameras that you own.

353
00:19:03,958 --> 00:19:06,294
I guess a good cabbage harvest brings in
lots of nonsense too.

354
00:19:07,262 --> 00:19:10,932
Officer Park.
You know how busy I am, right?

355
00:19:10,932 --> 00:19:13,735
He only had seedlings in his field,
but it's harvest season for us.

356
00:19:14,069 --> 00:19:16,905
We're already short on hands, so why
would I be wasting time with his cabbages?

357
00:19:16,905 --> 00:19:18,506
Put me on speaker.

358
00:19:23,745 --> 00:19:27,082
Have you ever seen a culprit
who hands over proof himself?

359
00:19:27,482 --> 00:19:28,683
Figure it out yourself.

360
00:19:28,917 --> 00:19:30,752
You won't show it because you're guilty.

361
00:19:31,086 --> 00:19:33,254
I'll find out the truth no matter what.

362
00:19:33,254 --> 00:19:34,255
I will.

363
00:19:35,957 --> 00:19:40,495
(Police)

364
00:19:43,665 --> 00:19:47,435
He should come to me if he needs it.
Does he think he's in control here?

365
00:20:03,852 --> 00:20:06,087
Is it really a human footprint?

366
00:20:08,289 --> 00:20:10,258
What if it's someone from Yeonri-ri?

367
00:20:13,895 --> 00:20:17,165
(Security Camera)

368
00:20:22,303 --> 00:20:24,806
Get a grip.

369
00:20:24,806 --> 00:20:25,840
What are you even thinking?

370
00:20:26,608 --> 00:20:28,877
There's no one in our village
who'd do something like that.

371
00:20:30,812 --> 00:20:32,514
Only wild boars or deer would do that.

372
00:20:32,514 --> 00:20:35,183
He doesn't know anything about farming.
Who is he to jump to conclusions?

373
00:20:52,967 --> 00:20:54,069
Will they be okay?

374
00:20:55,270 --> 00:20:56,237
Our dads.

375
00:20:57,739 --> 00:21:00,175
They looked like they were ready
to tear each other apart earlier.

376
00:21:01,509 --> 00:21:03,478
I've never seen my dad
like that before, either.

377
00:21:05,947 --> 00:21:09,284
My dad is usually easygoing
and laughs it off about everything.

378
00:21:09,284 --> 00:21:11,486
But he completely loses it
when it comes to Mat Story.

379
00:21:13,722 --> 00:21:15,090
I understand why, but still...

380
00:21:18,126 --> 00:21:19,227
Mat Story...

381
00:21:20,061 --> 00:21:22,263
It's a place my dad devoted
half his life to.

382
00:21:24,032 --> 00:21:25,400
Who knew that would happen?

383
00:21:30,271 --> 00:21:31,339
What you see...

384
00:21:32,941 --> 00:21:34,376
might not be the whole truth.

385
00:22:14,649 --> 00:22:17,385
I'm pretty sure it was the village chief.
So why is he acting so shameless?

386
00:22:18,853 --> 00:22:21,289
If it's not him,
then who else could it be?

387
00:22:23,058 --> 00:22:23,925
Wait a minute.

388
00:22:24,459 --> 00:22:25,827
Like the village chief said,

389
00:22:25,827 --> 00:22:27,829
everyone here has
a grudge against Mat Story.

390
00:22:28,663 --> 00:22:31,166
Everyone in this village sided with him...

391
00:22:31,166 --> 00:22:32,534
and shut me out before, right?

392
00:22:33,234 --> 00:22:34,069
Then...

393
00:22:35,470 --> 00:22:38,673
is it possible
that it wasn't the village chief?

394
00:22:44,112 --> 00:22:45,380
Think, Seong Tae Hun.

395
00:22:45,947 --> 00:22:46,915
Think.

396
00:22:48,049 --> 00:22:50,285
Lee Seon Ja, the village gossip.

397
00:22:50,285 --> 00:22:51,753
Lacks motive. Pass.

398
00:22:51,753 --> 00:22:53,388
Women's association leader Nam Hye Sun.

399
00:22:53,388 --> 00:22:54,856
Seeking revenge on behalf of her husband?

400
00:22:54,856 --> 00:22:56,091
No. Pass.

401
00:22:56,691 --> 00:22:57,892
Chief Im Ju Hyeong.

402
00:22:58,626 --> 00:22:59,994
I don't think it was him.

403
00:23:00,762 --> 00:23:02,964
Then the Rae sisters?

404
00:23:04,432 --> 00:23:06,234
They couldn't have done it by themselves.

405
00:23:08,002 --> 00:23:08,937
What if...

406
00:23:09,337 --> 00:23:12,974
everyone in this village
is in on it together?

407
00:23:40,068 --> 00:23:41,169
They're all in it together.

408
00:23:41,169 --> 00:23:42,237
If not...

409
00:23:42,237 --> 00:23:44,272
there's no reason not to show
the security camera footage.

410
00:24:02,957 --> 00:24:05,326
This must weigh 5-6 kilograms.

411
00:24:06,995 --> 00:24:08,930
He's using the same water that I use.

412
00:24:08,930 --> 00:24:10,932
And the soil doesn't seem
too different either.

413
00:24:10,932 --> 00:24:11,933
Why do the cabbages grow so well here?

414
00:24:14,602 --> 00:24:17,839
These can be harvested soon.

415
00:24:18,740 --> 00:24:22,844
Meanwhile, all the cabbages I have left
are about to die.

416
00:24:40,995 --> 00:24:42,864
They're firm, and the veins are clear.

417
00:24:44,132 --> 00:24:46,134
These are flawless cabbages.

418
00:24:52,040 --> 00:24:53,174
No matter what I do,

419
00:24:53,174 --> 00:24:55,410
I'd never do something
as filthy as Mat Story.

420
00:24:55,410 --> 00:24:57,178
I just wanted to grow
the cabbage successfully...

421
00:24:57,178 --> 00:24:59,748
to prove our village was innocent.

422
00:24:59,748 --> 00:25:00,915
So what did you just accuse me of?

423
00:25:00,915 --> 00:25:03,351
Destroying your field?

424
00:25:04,886 --> 00:25:07,789
That's right. Someone who's this serious
about farming cabbages...

425
00:25:07,789 --> 00:25:09,257
wouldn't ruin someone else's field.

426
00:25:11,826 --> 00:25:13,028
The village chief...

427
00:25:13,795 --> 00:25:15,296
may not be the culprit.

428
00:25:17,132 --> 00:25:19,034
I will expand the scope
of the investigation.

429
00:25:19,768 --> 00:25:23,004
I heard Ju Hyeong's farm had
a great cabbage harvest this year.

430
00:25:23,004 --> 00:25:25,273
Yes, I heard that too.
It was quite a huge success for him.

431
00:25:25,273 --> 00:25:26,808
When are you making kimchi?

432
00:25:26,808 --> 00:25:28,676
We need to harvest cabbage first.

433
00:25:28,676 --> 00:25:32,447
By the way, I heard
that Mat Story guy's field got torn up,

434
00:25:32,447 --> 00:25:33,815
and it's ruined now.

435
00:25:33,815 --> 00:25:34,649
Who?

436
00:25:34,649 --> 00:25:36,317
Come on.

437
00:25:37,152 --> 00:25:39,854
Someone destroyed his field,
and it's ruined now.

438
00:25:40,422 --> 00:25:41,990
How did that happen?

439
00:25:41,990 --> 00:25:43,825
In my opinion...

440
00:25:43,825 --> 00:25:44,592
Yes?

441
00:25:45,527 --> 00:25:46,361
What?

442
00:25:47,128 --> 00:25:49,698
I'm sure it's him.

443
00:25:49,698 --> 00:25:51,132
Him?

444
00:25:55,837 --> 00:25:57,038
They're all wearing similar-sized shoes.

445
00:26:10,385 --> 00:26:12,020
You really fell asleep right away?

446
00:26:13,822 --> 00:26:15,557
What?

447
00:26:17,826 --> 00:26:18,793
I'm here now.

448
00:26:20,161 --> 00:26:21,796
I have to go.

449
00:26:21,796 --> 00:26:23,198
I have to go inside.

450
00:26:23,198 --> 00:26:23,965
This big.

451
00:26:23,965 --> 00:26:24,866
I don't know.

452
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:26,501
I don't know.

453
00:26:27,802 --> 00:26:28,903
Okay. I'll call you.

454
00:26:29,938 --> 00:26:31,539
I'm here.

455
00:26:43,918 --> 00:26:45,153
- You're home?
- Yes.

456
00:26:45,153 --> 00:26:48,523
It's hard to see your face
around here these days.

457
00:26:49,624 --> 00:26:51,459
How's finding the culprit going?

458
00:26:51,459 --> 00:26:52,794
No luck at all?

459
00:26:53,094 --> 00:26:54,662
It's not easy.

460
00:26:55,997 --> 00:26:57,732
I should help somehow.

461
00:26:57,732 --> 00:26:58,600
It's okay.

462
00:27:01,436 --> 00:27:02,437
Are the kids asleep?

463
00:27:03,605 --> 00:27:04,406
Yes.

464
00:27:04,406 --> 00:27:05,840
Everything's fine at home, right?

465
00:27:06,374 --> 00:27:07,475
Everything's fine.

466
00:27:09,544 --> 00:27:12,914
But Ji Cheon's been acting
a bit strange lately.

467
00:27:13,748 --> 00:27:15,950
What about him?

468
00:27:16,518 --> 00:27:18,486
It's just... A woman's intuition.

469
00:27:20,855 --> 00:27:23,758
- I think something's bothering him.
- What do you mean?

470
00:27:23,758 --> 00:27:25,326
What could be bothering him?

471
00:27:25,326 --> 00:27:27,762
I'm tired. I'll go wash up first.

472
00:27:29,030 --> 00:27:29,864
Okay.

473
00:27:34,703 --> 00:27:36,938
Shall we make a toast?

474
00:27:36,938 --> 00:27:38,540
- Okay.
- Let's toast.

475
00:27:38,540 --> 00:27:39,808
Cheers.

476
00:27:44,479 --> 00:27:45,547
Dad.

477
00:27:45,547 --> 00:27:48,783
Dad, you should really start working out.

478
00:27:48,783 --> 00:27:50,318
Your belly's gotten bigger lately.

479
00:27:50,318 --> 00:27:53,188
It's as big as Mount Rushmore.

480
00:27:53,188 --> 00:27:55,590
You're the one always bringing home
spicy rice cakes.

481
00:27:55,590 --> 00:27:57,325
That's why I gained weight.

482
00:27:57,325 --> 00:27:59,294
No, it's the alcohol.

483
00:27:59,494 --> 00:28:02,330
Rice cakes don't make you gain weight.

484
00:28:02,330 --> 00:28:04,599
I'm thirsty.

485
00:28:05,934 --> 00:28:07,802
Princess, would you like a drink?

486
00:28:07,802 --> 00:28:09,671
Sure.

487
00:28:10,905 --> 00:28:13,475
Don't drink too much, Mom. Okay?

488
00:28:13,475 --> 00:28:15,944
Please. This is non-alcoholic.

489
00:28:17,278 --> 00:28:18,179
Bo Mi.

490
00:28:18,513 --> 00:28:20,415
With how late you've been coming home,

491
00:28:20,415 --> 00:28:24,119
it feels just like when you were dating
that guy with glasses.

492
00:28:24,119 --> 00:28:25,720
Are you seeing someone?

493
00:28:25,720 --> 00:28:28,690
Dad, thanks to you, I broke up
with him just after two months.

494
00:28:28,690 --> 00:28:31,593
Whom can I date because of you?

495
00:28:31,993 --> 00:28:32,961
He was a loser.

496
00:28:33,728 --> 00:28:35,597
He had no guts.

497
00:28:36,264 --> 00:28:38,299
Since we're on the topic, let's hear it.

498
00:28:40,702 --> 00:28:43,605
Ms. Im Bo Mi, what's your ideal type?

499
00:29:06,394 --> 00:29:07,328
Well...

500
00:29:08,496 --> 00:29:09,931
Either he looks handsome only to me,

501
00:29:10,532 --> 00:29:12,534
or he's handsome to everyone.

502
00:29:13,468 --> 00:29:15,203
So basically, he just needs to be a guy?

503
00:29:15,203 --> 00:29:17,672
Then go to Seoul.

504
00:29:18,006 --> 00:29:19,541
There are plenty of men there.

505
00:29:19,541 --> 00:29:21,443
Don't be ridiculous.

506
00:29:22,210 --> 00:29:24,212
How can we let her go to Seoul alone?

507
00:29:24,212 --> 00:29:25,814
She's all grown up now.

508
00:29:25,814 --> 00:29:26,881
Whatever.

509
00:29:27,215 --> 00:29:28,416
Hey, did you know?

510
00:29:29,484 --> 00:29:31,720
Your mom only cared about looks
when choosing a man too.

511
00:29:46,368 --> 00:29:47,836
Are you asleep, Ji Cheon?

512
00:29:53,608 --> 00:29:54,442
No.

513
00:29:58,980 --> 00:30:01,082
Bo Mi, you're not asleep...

514
00:30:01,082 --> 00:30:02,851
I forgot to tell you earlier.

515
00:30:02,851 --> 00:30:05,186
Kids have
their outdoor soccer class tomorrow.

516
00:30:05,186 --> 00:30:07,689
We need to prepare snacks for them,
so come in an hour earlier.

517
00:30:16,297 --> 00:30:18,099
So...

518
00:30:18,666 --> 00:30:20,135
About us...

519
00:30:21,736 --> 00:30:22,670
Good night.

520
00:30:30,712 --> 00:30:31,646
What's wrong with him?

521
00:30:32,280 --> 00:30:34,215
He should reply right away
after reading my messages.

522
00:30:35,917 --> 00:30:36,985
Fine. I won't reply either.

523
00:30:37,585 --> 00:30:39,120
When a man kisses a woman,

524
00:30:39,120 --> 00:30:41,256
he should at least follow up on it.

525
00:30:41,256 --> 00:30:43,925
He hasn't said a word since then.
He's just acting cautious.

526
00:30:45,160 --> 00:30:46,594
Is he testing the waters or what?

527
00:30:47,362 --> 00:30:49,531
Shouldn't he at least realize
that I was the one who messaged him first?

528
00:30:52,667 --> 00:30:55,103
He's the one who made the move
without signaling first.

529
00:30:56,438 --> 00:30:58,306
This is basically a hit-and-run!

530
00:31:34,376 --> 00:31:35,643
Sir.

531
00:31:35,643 --> 00:31:39,614
What did you talk about with her earlier?

532
00:31:39,614 --> 00:31:40,515
What?

533
00:31:43,685 --> 00:31:47,422
What did you talk about with her earlier?

534
00:31:48,590 --> 00:31:49,557
You.

535
00:31:50,759 --> 00:31:54,095
They say you only see
what you want to see.

536
00:31:54,496 --> 00:31:56,531
We keep going back and forth on
how we feel about Mat Story.

537
00:31:56,531 --> 00:31:59,000
But you're behaving poorly these days.

538
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:02,270
Stirring up the entire village
like this...

539
00:32:02,270 --> 00:32:03,505
Did you think no one would notice?

540
00:32:05,740 --> 00:32:09,477
There's a saying. Give one more rice cake
to the person you dislike.

541
00:32:10,145 --> 00:32:12,147
Here. Eat this.

542
00:32:12,914 --> 00:32:13,748
Come with me.

543
00:32:21,690 --> 00:32:25,393
(Cafe Sunny)

544
00:32:30,131 --> 00:32:31,299
You're here.

545
00:32:31,733 --> 00:32:32,967
Look.

546
00:32:32,967 --> 00:32:34,569
I brought some extra help.

547
00:32:40,408 --> 00:32:42,610
Don't just stand there. Sit down.

548
00:32:43,878 --> 00:32:46,047
When you were chasing us around,

549
00:32:46,047 --> 00:32:49,417
you were hopping here and there
like a little rabbit.

550
00:32:49,417 --> 00:32:51,453
So why are you standing there
like a stick now, spacing out?

551
00:32:52,687 --> 00:32:55,090
Like father, like son.

552
00:32:55,090 --> 00:32:56,324
You two are the same.

553
00:32:58,259 --> 00:32:59,227
Mr. Seong.

554
00:32:59,928 --> 00:33:02,430
You should pay for causing trouble
for the entire village.

555
00:33:03,064 --> 00:33:04,966
Sit down and start shelling peanuts.

556
00:33:05,667 --> 00:33:07,235
You see that sign over there?

557
00:33:07,235 --> 00:33:08,803
Our cafe's new menu.

558
00:33:08,803 --> 00:33:09,904
Peanut latte.

559
00:33:09,904 --> 00:33:12,407
(Peanut latte launched)

560
00:33:19,714 --> 00:33:21,116
If you don't pay me enough, I won't do it.

561
00:33:24,519 --> 00:33:25,387
So...

562
00:33:26,287 --> 00:33:29,491
If you have something to say,
please go ahead.

563
00:33:32,827 --> 00:33:35,597
Aren't you the one
who has something to say?

564
00:33:37,232 --> 00:33:38,366
Did you do something wrong?

565
00:33:39,300 --> 00:33:42,203
You said he's the one at fault.
Why are you acting like you're guilty?

566
00:33:44,272 --> 00:33:46,408
If you feel guilty about something,

567
00:33:46,408 --> 00:33:48,009
let's just call it even.

568
00:33:49,477 --> 00:33:52,747
We're sorry for not giving you
a proper welcome.

569
00:33:55,884 --> 00:33:58,486
But your field...

570
00:33:58,720 --> 00:34:02,023
It couldn't have been someone
from Yeonri-ri.

571
00:34:02,991 --> 00:34:06,161
You're a farmer now too,
so you understand, don't you?

572
00:34:06,995 --> 00:34:11,199
Growing crops with your own hands,
caring for them...

573
00:34:11,199 --> 00:34:13,568
It's just like raising your own child.

574
00:34:14,169 --> 00:34:18,807
That's why you're going through
all this trouble,

575
00:34:19,007 --> 00:34:22,110
trying to catch whoever did it.

576
00:34:23,411 --> 00:34:27,682
No matter what happens,
a farmer would never...

577
00:34:28,083 --> 00:34:30,218
harm something they raised.

578
00:34:36,624 --> 00:34:37,592
That's right.

579
00:34:39,427 --> 00:34:40,562
Mak Dung.

580
00:34:44,332 --> 00:34:47,469
It feels like it's been a while since...

581
00:34:47,969 --> 00:34:49,504
I heard our youngest's voice.

582
00:34:55,043 --> 00:34:56,211
Mak Rae.

583
00:34:56,211 --> 00:34:59,347
She's always forgetful
because she takes after me.

584
00:34:59,881 --> 00:35:02,183
There are still a lot of peanuts left.
Let's hurry up and shell them.

585
00:35:02,183 --> 00:35:03,918
Okay.

586
00:35:06,221 --> 00:35:08,523
If life just went smoothly
the way you wanted,

587
00:35:08,523 --> 00:35:09,691
would that even be life?

588
00:35:11,192 --> 00:35:13,428
If there are sunny days,
there are also rainy days.

589
00:35:15,130 --> 00:35:18,400
From what I can see, I think the heavens
sent you here on purpose.

590
00:35:19,501 --> 00:35:22,037
So you can learn about life while farming.

591
00:36:18,159 --> 00:36:19,861
Bo Mi, after work today...

592
00:36:22,330 --> 00:36:23,698
We're late.

593
00:36:23,698 --> 00:36:24,632
Let's get going.

594
00:36:30,872 --> 00:36:33,241
Just receive the ball like this, okay?

595
00:36:33,241 --> 00:36:35,343
Just push it lightly to pass the ball.

596
00:36:35,343 --> 00:36:36,211
Pass.

597
00:36:36,211 --> 00:36:37,245
Yes.

598
00:36:37,245 --> 00:36:39,147
Throw it back to me.

599
00:36:41,449 --> 00:36:42,217
Pass.

600
00:36:42,217 --> 00:36:43,618
Again. Pass.

601
00:36:44,019 --> 00:36:45,453
Lightly. That's it.

602
00:36:46,087 --> 00:36:46,955
Here.

603
00:36:46,955 --> 00:36:48,223
They call that soccer?

604
00:36:50,125 --> 00:36:51,793
Why don't you try it too? Here.

605
00:36:52,460 --> 00:36:54,362
Pass the ball. Pass it to me.

606
00:36:54,829 --> 00:36:55,797
Yes.

607
00:36:57,799 --> 00:36:59,567
Ji Gu, pass.

608
00:37:03,338 --> 00:37:04,205
Pass.

609
00:37:08,476 --> 00:37:09,177
Ji Gu.

610
00:37:10,345 --> 00:37:11,780
Why don't you try kicking the ball
to your classmates?

611
00:37:12,580 --> 00:37:15,483
Put some strength on the side
of your foot and tap it like this.

612
00:37:17,485 --> 00:37:18,653
It's okay. Try it.

613
00:37:21,589 --> 00:37:22,691
Yes.

614
00:37:23,191 --> 00:37:24,592
That was great.

615
00:37:24,592 --> 00:37:26,494
Let's play together. Come here.

616
00:37:27,028 --> 00:37:28,163
Let's play together.

617
00:37:28,163 --> 00:37:29,764
Guys, why don't we play together?

618
00:37:29,764 --> 00:37:31,666
Ji Sang. You come here too.

619
00:37:32,500 --> 00:37:33,535
Come on.

620
00:37:33,535 --> 00:37:35,437
Let's make a wider circle.

621
00:37:35,437 --> 00:37:37,105
Yes, good.

622
00:37:37,105 --> 00:37:38,873
Step back a little.

623
00:37:41,609 --> 00:37:42,844
Pass it over here.

624
00:37:45,146 --> 00:37:46,781
- Bo Mi.
- Hi.

625
00:37:47,482 --> 00:37:48,316
Hi.

626
00:37:48,583 --> 00:37:49,651
You're hard at work.

627
00:37:50,185 --> 00:37:51,219
Officer Park?

628
00:37:53,021 --> 00:37:56,658
He's the soccer class instructor.

629
00:37:57,025 --> 00:37:59,327
He volunteers like this for the kids
every time he's off duty.

630
00:37:59,327 --> 00:38:00,362
Isn't he really cool?

631
00:38:16,945 --> 00:38:17,812
Good.

632
00:38:25,353 --> 00:38:26,521
Pass.

633
00:38:37,232 --> 00:38:38,199
That was great.

634
00:38:47,409 --> 00:38:48,243
Pass.

635
00:38:49,144 --> 00:38:50,045
Good job.

636
00:38:55,417 --> 00:38:56,317
Shoot.

637
00:39:10,065 --> 00:39:11,466
Goal!

638
00:39:14,602 --> 00:39:16,504
- Good job. Do you want some more?
- Bye.

639
00:39:16,504 --> 00:39:18,406
- Go enjoy your food.
- Bye.

640
00:39:18,406 --> 00:39:19,774
Would you like one more, Ji Sang?

641
00:39:19,774 --> 00:39:20,742
Enjoy.

642
00:39:20,742 --> 00:39:21,776
- This is for you.
- Thank you.

643
00:39:21,776 --> 00:39:22,677
Good work.

644
00:39:22,677 --> 00:39:24,679
Everything's gone.
You had a lot earlier too, right?

645
00:39:24,979 --> 00:39:25,847
Bye.

646
00:39:29,150 --> 00:39:32,020
Be sure to ice your legs before you sleep.

647
00:39:33,154 --> 00:39:35,123
Otherwise, you'll be sore tomorrow.

648
00:39:36,358 --> 00:39:37,826
I know a thing or two
about muscles myself.

649
00:39:38,727 --> 00:39:40,495
Next time, let's go up
against each other properly.

650
00:39:40,995 --> 00:39:41,930
One-on-one.

651
00:39:54,342 --> 00:39:55,276
Hi, Dad.

652
00:39:57,679 --> 00:39:58,713
Officer Park?

653
00:39:59,547 --> 00:40:01,082
Yes, he's still here with me.

654
00:40:02,584 --> 00:40:03,718
What? Today?

655
00:40:12,360 --> 00:40:13,895
This is ginseng liquor.

656
00:40:14,362 --> 00:40:16,531
I'm opening this for the first time
in ten years.

657
00:40:16,531 --> 00:40:17,932
- Hand me your glass.
- Okay.

658
00:40:21,336 --> 00:40:24,339
You're working extra hard these days
because of that troublemaker.

659
00:40:25,306 --> 00:40:28,043
You went through a lot of trouble
because of that security camera incident.

660
00:40:28,410 --> 00:40:29,711
Not at all, sir.

661
00:40:30,178 --> 00:40:31,346
Would you like a glass too, Bo Mi?

662
00:40:32,013 --> 00:40:34,015
I don't really like ginseng liquor.

663
00:40:34,015 --> 00:40:35,817
Bo Mi, you're more of a beer person,
aren't you?

664
00:40:36,217 --> 00:40:38,319
Is there beer in the fridge?
I'll go grab one.

665
00:40:38,319 --> 00:40:39,754
No. Just stay put.

666
00:40:39,754 --> 00:40:41,856
You just sit and enjoy.

667
00:40:41,856 --> 00:40:43,958
A mother-in-law is all about
doting on her son-in-law, right?

668
00:40:43,958 --> 00:40:45,527
It may not be a prized hen,

669
00:40:45,527 --> 00:40:47,962
but we did get fried chicken for you.

670
00:40:48,963 --> 00:40:50,565
Nam Hye Sun.

671
00:40:51,833 --> 00:40:53,802
Go bring a bottle of beer.

672
00:40:56,504 --> 00:40:58,106
What? Don't you have hands?

673
00:40:58,540 --> 00:41:00,341
No, I'll go get one.

674
00:41:00,341 --> 00:41:01,743
Wait right here, Bo Mi.

675
00:41:02,977 --> 00:41:05,447
How sweet.

676
00:41:07,449 --> 00:41:08,483
Is it the liquor?

677
00:41:09,384 --> 00:41:10,952
What's sweet?

678
00:41:11,753 --> 00:41:13,655
All I smell is greasy food.

679
00:41:13,655 --> 00:41:15,790
Dad, stop it. Are you drunk?

680
00:41:15,790 --> 00:41:17,025
I'm not drunk.

681
00:41:19,260 --> 00:41:20,195
Thank you.

682
00:41:22,030 --> 00:41:24,933
See? He looks strong opening the bottle.

683
00:41:24,933 --> 00:41:25,767
Bo Mi, here.

684
00:41:35,510 --> 00:41:38,346
What are they talking about?
Why do they sound so happy?

685
00:41:44,052 --> 00:41:44,886
Father.

686
00:41:45,487 --> 00:41:46,955
Please let me marry your daughter.

687
00:41:47,822 --> 00:41:50,992
I will make Bo Mi happy
for the rest of her life.

688
00:41:57,832 --> 00:41:59,200
My son-in-law.

689
00:42:03,772 --> 00:42:04,606
Bo Mi.

690
00:42:09,244 --> 00:42:10,111
My goodness.

691
00:42:15,684 --> 00:42:16,518
No.

692
00:42:17,919 --> 00:42:21,022
Only Hye Sun was ignoring me.

693
00:42:21,956 --> 00:42:23,958
A woman like that is ignoring me?

694
00:42:23,958 --> 00:42:25,360
There was this aura shining around her.

695
00:42:26,227 --> 00:42:28,363
You know what an aura is?

696
00:42:30,265 --> 00:42:32,934
Who is it? Who's being so impatient?

697
00:42:32,934 --> 00:42:34,969
Who's ringing the bell like that?

698
00:42:34,969 --> 00:42:36,404
- Go see who it is.
- I'll go.

699
00:42:36,404 --> 00:42:37,605
Where was I?

700
00:42:38,039 --> 00:42:39,374
Who is it?

701
00:42:39,374 --> 00:42:41,276
An aura. I was talking about an aura.

702
00:42:43,044 --> 00:42:43,945
Bo Mi.

703
00:42:48,717 --> 00:42:50,318
Who's at the door?

704
00:42:50,318 --> 00:42:51,252
Is it Dong Sik?

705
00:42:52,287 --> 00:42:54,422
Ji Cheon, what are you doing here?

706
00:42:54,422 --> 00:42:55,924
Who is it?

707
00:42:56,191 --> 00:42:58,126
Is it Dong Sik? Tell him to come in.

708
00:42:58,126 --> 00:43:00,562
No, it's not him.

709
00:43:12,307 --> 00:43:13,975
You scared me.

710
00:43:13,975 --> 00:43:15,076
Is something wrong?

711
00:43:15,877 --> 00:43:17,779
Yes, it's urgent.

712
00:43:17,779 --> 00:43:18,813
Urgent?

713
00:43:19,114 --> 00:43:21,149
Then you should've called.

714
00:43:21,349 --> 00:43:23,184
It was too urgent, so I just ran here.

715
00:43:24,452 --> 00:43:26,321
Bo Mi, about that kiss...

716
00:43:28,223 --> 00:43:29,391
What kiss?

717
00:43:29,657 --> 00:43:31,192
When did we ever kiss?

718
00:43:31,726 --> 00:43:33,294
That time, by the wall
in the apple orchard...

719
00:43:33,294 --> 00:43:35,663
That wasn't a kiss.

720
00:43:36,598 --> 00:43:37,565
A headbutt.

721
00:43:38,199 --> 00:43:39,801
- A headbutt?
- Yes.

722
00:43:39,801 --> 00:43:40,835
A lip headbutt.

723
00:43:42,837 --> 00:43:45,573
Anyway... What about it?

724
00:43:45,874 --> 00:43:48,276
That was so long ago. Why bring it up now?

725
00:43:48,276 --> 00:43:49,944
That's why I wanted to tell you this
before it's too late.

726
00:43:53,915 --> 00:43:54,916
That kiss...

727
00:43:55,650 --> 00:43:56,618
No, that peck...

728
00:43:57,986 --> 00:43:59,254
It wasn't a mistake.

729
00:44:00,922 --> 00:44:01,756
What?

730
00:44:02,791 --> 00:44:03,858
It wasn't a mistake.

731
00:44:06,261 --> 00:44:07,462
I meant it.

732
00:44:13,568 --> 00:44:15,937
I don't like how Officer Park keeps
coming over to see you.

733
00:44:16,471 --> 00:44:19,074
And I don't like seeing him laughing
with your father at your house.

734
00:44:19,941 --> 00:44:21,076
So what I mean is...

735
00:44:23,878 --> 00:44:24,813
What I mean is...

736
00:44:32,587 --> 00:44:34,222
So what's your point?

737
00:44:37,025 --> 00:44:38,226
I think I like you.

738
00:44:40,462 --> 00:44:42,664
I mean, I like you, Bo Mi.

739
00:44:53,375 --> 00:44:54,676
Seriously.

740
00:45:02,417 --> 00:45:04,352
What a relief. It wasn't a hit-and-run.

741
00:45:05,653 --> 00:45:06,688
A hit-and-run?

742
00:45:06,688 --> 00:45:09,858
Yes, something like a hit-and-run.

743
00:45:23,872 --> 00:45:25,140
Your call is forwarded to...

744
00:45:27,809 --> 00:45:30,612
She's not answering her phone.
Where did she go?

745
00:45:52,967 --> 00:45:53,835
Bo Mi.

746
00:46:13,955 --> 00:46:15,924
Why did Dong Sik come? Is something wrong?

747
00:46:16,591 --> 00:46:18,026
What? Dong Sik?

748
00:46:18,293 --> 00:46:19,194
Yes.

749
00:46:19,627 --> 00:46:22,697
Officer Park said
you were talking to Dong Sik.

750
00:46:23,465 --> 00:46:26,434
He told us
that he said goodbye to you...

751
00:46:26,434 --> 00:46:28,303
because he has to go to work
tomorrow morning.

752
00:46:28,303 --> 00:46:30,572
He went home soon after that.

753
00:46:31,206 --> 00:46:32,540
Is that right?

754
00:46:34,042 --> 00:46:35,810
Right.

755
00:46:35,810 --> 00:46:38,113
I guess Dong Sik has some concerns
these days.

756
00:46:39,514 --> 00:46:40,782
Concerns?

757
00:46:40,782 --> 00:46:43,018
Dong Sik has concerns?

758
00:46:43,018 --> 00:46:45,920
He's all grown up now.

759
00:46:45,920 --> 00:46:48,023
Don't you know how old he is?

760
00:46:48,023 --> 00:46:49,524
He's been all grown up for a while now.

761
00:46:49,824 --> 00:46:51,860
What about you?

762
00:46:54,029 --> 00:46:56,698
Until when are you going to live
like this?

763
00:46:57,365 --> 00:47:00,135
See? Because you are living like this,

764
00:47:00,135 --> 00:47:03,238
your dad is trying to set you up
with Officer Park.

765
00:47:03,238 --> 00:47:04,839
There you go again, Ms. Nam.

766
00:47:04,839 --> 00:47:06,875
Why are we talking about me
out of the blue?

767
00:47:07,442 --> 00:47:09,044
Since we're on the topic, sit down.

768
00:47:09,044 --> 00:47:10,345
I'm tired.

769
00:47:10,345 --> 00:47:11,713
Come on.

770
00:47:11,713 --> 00:47:14,015
My goodness. Look at the time.
I must go to bed now.

771
00:47:14,683 --> 00:47:15,650
Bo Mi.

772
00:47:15,650 --> 00:47:17,852
Dad, go sleep in your room.

773
00:47:17,852 --> 00:47:18,720
Okay?

774
00:47:19,354 --> 00:47:20,989
Mom, I'm going to bed now. Good night.

775
00:47:20,989 --> 00:47:22,590
You're unbelievable.

776
00:47:22,590 --> 00:47:24,192
Im Bo Mi.

777
00:47:29,864 --> 00:47:30,865
Go sleep in the room.

778
00:48:30,859 --> 00:48:32,160
What are you doing?

779
00:48:33,495 --> 00:48:34,963
There are so many people watching.

780
00:48:37,032 --> 00:48:38,299
Then...

781
00:48:38,767 --> 00:48:40,702
That's not what I meant.

782
00:48:41,736 --> 00:48:42,737
Seong Ji Cheon.

783
00:48:43,405 --> 00:48:46,741
You can't take back anything now.

784
00:48:49,210 --> 00:48:50,178
You can't either.

785
00:48:51,346 --> 00:48:53,915
Shall we sit for a bit?

786
00:48:54,549 --> 00:48:55,350
Okay.

787
00:49:05,727 --> 00:49:07,362
Being here at ease...

788
00:49:08,830 --> 00:49:10,031
It feels a bit strange.

789
00:49:13,768 --> 00:49:15,136
When I was in Seoul,

790
00:49:15,970 --> 00:49:18,406
all I knew was how to endure
and push through.

791
00:49:20,475 --> 00:49:22,143
I didn't know how to let things out.

792
00:49:26,314 --> 00:49:27,949
When things got hard or suffocating,

793
00:49:29,584 --> 00:49:30,885
I thought I couldn't lean on anyone,

794
00:49:31,920 --> 00:49:34,789
not even my family.

795
00:49:38,026 --> 00:49:38,927
But...

796
00:49:41,096 --> 00:49:42,797
after meeting you, for the first time,

797
00:49:45,033 --> 00:49:46,901
I feel like I'm facing my real self.

798
00:49:49,270 --> 00:49:50,238
Thank you.

799
00:49:52,841 --> 00:49:55,076
You're in trouble now, Seong Ji Cheon.

800
00:49:55,076 --> 00:49:55,910
What?

801
00:49:56,478 --> 00:50:01,049
You haven't even seen
0.000000001% of my charm yet.

802
00:50:03,051 --> 00:50:05,086
At this rate, you might end up...

803
00:50:05,086 --> 00:50:06,821
liking me more than your mom soon.

804
00:50:07,822 --> 00:50:08,857
That's a bit...

805
00:50:10,125 --> 00:50:12,293
What? You're making me feel awkward.

806
00:50:12,827 --> 00:50:15,530
Come on. Say you like me again.
You said so yesterday.

807
00:50:19,067 --> 00:50:20,035
I...

808
00:50:22,904 --> 00:50:23,738
I...

809
00:50:25,273 --> 00:50:26,341
Where are you going?

810
00:50:49,431 --> 00:50:52,200
(Yeonri Branch, Manager Seong Tae Hun)

811
00:50:55,003 --> 00:50:57,639
(Must know confidential context,
internal data needs organizing?)

812
00:50:57,639 --> 00:50:59,207
(Why is Mat Story...)

813
00:51:12,654 --> 00:51:14,622
Hi, Mr. Jeong.

814
00:51:14,622 --> 00:51:16,691
I'm sorry to call you so late, Mr. Seong.

815
00:51:16,991 --> 00:51:19,294
That Yeonri branch manager
you mentioned...

816
00:51:19,294 --> 00:51:21,196
when you came to Seoul last time...

817
00:51:21,763 --> 00:51:24,766
I looked into it, and officially...

818
00:51:25,734 --> 00:51:26,701
there is no manager.

819
00:51:27,902 --> 00:51:31,473
It seems like it's connected
to Mr. Choi...

820
00:51:31,473 --> 00:51:34,242
Either way, I think you should
be careful of that manager too.

821
00:51:34,743 --> 00:51:36,978
He might be monitoring you...

822
00:51:37,612 --> 00:51:39,948
or maybe Mr. Choi planted him
to interfere...

823
00:51:39,948 --> 00:51:40,815
Interfere?

824
00:51:41,683 --> 00:51:43,385
The company is sending...

825
00:51:43,385 --> 00:51:45,487
a truck tomorrow to pick up the samples.

826
00:51:45,487 --> 00:51:48,189
No, I'll take them to Seoul myself.

827
00:51:48,189 --> 00:51:49,290
I can't let anything happen to them.

828
00:51:50,592 --> 00:51:52,293
(Yeonri-ri)

829
00:51:54,696 --> 00:51:55,597
You're excused.

830
00:51:58,199 --> 00:52:00,602
Why didn't I think of that?

831
00:52:00,602 --> 00:52:01,636
Thanks, Mr. Jeong.

832
00:52:01,636 --> 00:52:03,238
I'll call you back later.

833
00:52:07,909 --> 00:52:08,777
That's right.

834
00:52:09,344 --> 00:52:11,446
It wasn't just the villagers
who were against me.

835
00:52:12,080 --> 00:52:13,882
It was Mr. Choi...

836
00:52:14,282 --> 00:52:15,517
who sent me here in the first place.

837
00:52:18,253 --> 00:52:19,354
Mr. Bae.

838
00:52:19,354 --> 00:52:22,357
Mr. Bae said he sent me here
with a bigger purpose,

839
00:52:22,357 --> 00:52:23,792
but that was his intention.

840
00:52:24,459 --> 00:52:27,562
Mr. Choi might actually want me to fail.

841
00:52:28,396 --> 00:52:30,832
If the executive gave an order...

842
00:52:30,832 --> 00:52:32,233
to develop the Yeonri branch,

843
00:52:32,734 --> 00:52:35,003
and someone had to be sent...

844
00:52:37,639 --> 00:52:39,574
The company needs you there.

845
00:52:39,574 --> 00:52:40,809
Are you refusing to go?

846
00:52:41,710 --> 00:52:43,678
Within one month, send seedling samples.

847
00:52:43,678 --> 00:52:45,780
I want 300 of each sample,

848
00:52:45,780 --> 00:52:47,515
so 1,500 total.

849
00:52:52,487 --> 00:52:54,823
What if he sent a thorn in his side...

850
00:52:55,290 --> 00:52:58,059
and designed it to fail from the start?

851
00:53:02,997 --> 00:53:06,134
There was a reason
the results of the seedling samples...

852
00:53:06,134 --> 00:53:07,268
haven't come out all this time.

853
00:53:11,573 --> 00:53:15,009
When are you planning to inform
Mr. Seong the results?

854
00:53:15,009 --> 00:53:16,578
If we're going to change the purpose,

855
00:53:16,911 --> 00:53:18,413
there isn't much time left.

856
00:53:18,680 --> 00:53:20,448
It's time to set sail.

857
00:53:21,082 --> 00:53:22,517
I'll raise anchor soon.

858
00:53:23,685 --> 00:53:25,587
I'll inform him
that the samples were rejected...

859
00:53:25,587 --> 00:53:27,555
and make it clear that
what he should really be doing...

860
00:53:28,189 --> 00:53:30,592
isn't playing around with cabbages.

861
00:53:36,564 --> 00:53:38,166
(Analysis Report)

862
00:53:38,166 --> 00:53:41,436
(Unqualified)

863
00:53:59,788 --> 00:54:01,356
(Missed calls)

864
00:54:10,131 --> 00:54:12,300
You thought I wouldn't find you?

865
00:54:12,300 --> 00:54:14,803
You thought hiding in some rural town
in Korea would keep me from finding you?

866
00:54:14,803 --> 00:54:17,706
What am I going to do?

867
00:54:33,822 --> 00:54:37,492
The cabbages are fully grown.

868
00:54:37,959 --> 00:54:40,328
Forget that.
We have to harvest everything today.

869
00:54:40,628 --> 00:54:42,464
- All right.
- We're running late.

870
00:54:42,464 --> 00:54:44,399
You're harvesting these cabbages
a bit early this year.

871
00:54:46,701 --> 00:54:49,104
It got cold a bit earlier than usual.

872
00:54:49,104 --> 00:54:52,107
Let's meet next time as kimchi, guys.

873
00:54:53,875 --> 00:54:54,876
My back.

874
00:54:56,411 --> 00:54:58,847
I could really eat some boiled pork
right now.

875
00:54:58,847 --> 00:55:00,081
You're buying the meat, okay?

876
00:55:00,081 --> 00:55:01,282
What do you mean?

877
00:55:05,920 --> 00:55:06,788
What?

878
00:55:11,026 --> 00:55:12,627
What's he trying to do?

879
00:55:13,261 --> 00:55:14,095
Chief.

880
00:55:14,729 --> 00:55:16,765
It looks like he's trying to fix up
that field again.

881
00:55:18,433 --> 00:55:21,069
Go ahead and try to ruin it.

882
00:55:21,636 --> 00:55:22,837
Seong Tae Hun cabbages.

883
00:55:23,438 --> 00:55:25,473
I'll grow them no matter what.

884
00:55:25,740 --> 00:55:27,575
I will definitely...

885
00:55:28,977 --> 00:55:31,046
grow them.

886
00:55:32,414 --> 00:55:33,715
I won't ever give up.

887
00:55:36,284 --> 00:55:38,586
Seong Tae Hun cabbages.

888
00:55:47,862 --> 00:55:50,398
He's really stubborn.

889
00:56:04,212 --> 00:56:06,381
We didn't do anything wrong.
So what's there to be afraid of?

890
00:56:07,716 --> 00:56:09,951
Why make all the villagers
out to be criminals?

891
00:56:11,786 --> 00:56:14,923
I'll watch the footage...

892
00:56:15,824 --> 00:56:18,293
and prove that it wasn't us.

893
00:56:23,898 --> 00:56:26,601
(Security Camera)

894
00:56:44,352 --> 00:56:45,954
If he's watching me again today,

895
00:56:45,954 --> 00:56:47,389
he'll definitely come back.

896
00:56:50,592 --> 00:56:53,628
His goal must be to destroy
all the living seedlings.

897
00:56:53,628 --> 00:56:55,997
So he'll definitely come back.

898
00:56:59,434 --> 00:57:01,269
Will he be home late again today?

899
00:57:03,038 --> 00:57:04,472
Should I call him?

900
00:57:13,882 --> 00:57:15,116
Let's go to bed.

901
00:57:58,093 --> 00:58:00,195
Hey! Stop right there!

902
00:58:01,096 --> 00:58:02,797
I'll catch you no matter what!

903
00:58:02,797 --> 00:58:03,631
Stop right there!

904
00:58:04,399 --> 00:58:05,266
Hey.

905
00:58:11,272 --> 00:58:12,273
In that moment,

906
00:58:14,709 --> 00:58:16,778
maybe I was hoping it wasn't true.

907
00:58:18,380 --> 00:58:19,447
Who is it?

908
00:58:25,987 --> 00:58:28,723
That my gut feeling was wrong.

909
00:58:36,798 --> 00:58:40,068
I was so focused on the cabbages
that I didn't know...

910
00:58:40,902 --> 00:58:42,237
that rather than the sincerity
I had carried all this time,

911
00:58:43,605 --> 00:58:44,906
the truth that was about to hit me...

912
00:58:47,308 --> 00:58:48,209
was...

913
00:58:49,444 --> 00:58:50,712
more frightening.

914
00:59:20,542 --> 00:59:23,545
(Cabbage Your Life)

915
00:59:23,545 --> 00:59:24,846
You watched
the camera footage, didn't you?

916
00:59:24,846 --> 00:59:26,114
The camera footage is useless.

917
00:59:26,114 --> 00:59:28,083
I won't believe the culprit
is someone from Yeonri-ri,

918
00:59:28,083 --> 00:59:29,784
no matter what.

919
00:59:29,784 --> 00:59:30,985
The same goes for me.

920
00:59:30,985 --> 00:59:33,021
I don't want to believe that...

921
00:59:33,021 --> 00:59:34,989
all of this is Mat Story
trying to push me out.

922
00:59:34,989 --> 00:59:36,558
Let me try. I'll use the knife.

923
00:59:36,558 --> 00:59:39,327
I can't keep avoiding it forever.

924
00:59:39,327 --> 00:59:40,995
I'm trying to find the right path.

925
00:59:40,995 --> 00:59:42,831
I'm sorry, honey.

926
00:59:42,831 --> 00:59:44,733
But it's better than stealing, right?

927
00:59:44,733 --> 00:59:46,668
I saw Cho Mi Ryeo on my way here.

928
00:59:46,668 --> 00:59:47,836
Something seemed really off.

929
00:59:47,836 --> 00:59:49,771
Something's definitely going on.

930
00:59:49,771 --> 00:59:51,940
Then you just need to find
the real culprit.

931
00:59:51,940 --> 00:59:53,942
You and me together.

932
00:59:53,942 --> 00:59:55,076
Let's catch the culprit together.

933
00:59:55,610 --> 00:59:57,612
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
